1️⃣8️⃣ What is Race Condition?
Answer:
Occurs when multiple threads access shared data simultaneously and the outcome depends on thread execution order.

What is thread starvation?
Answer:
When a thread never gets CPU time due to priority or lock issues.


✅ 50. What is Thread.sleep()? Does it release locks?
Thread.sleep(2000);
✔️ Meaning:
Pauses the current thread for given time (milliseconds)
Moves thread to TIMED WAITING state

❌ NO — it does NOT release locks


✅ 49. Create 2 threads — one sleeps, one runs
✔️ Code (Simple & Clean)
class SleepThread extends Thread {
    public void run() {
        try {
            System.out.println("SleepThread started");
            Thread.sleep(2000); // sleep for 2 seconds
            System.out.println("SleepThread woke up");
        } catch (InterruptedException e) {
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

class RunThread extends Thread {
    public void run() {
        System.out.println("RunThread is running");
    }
}

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        SleepThread t1 = new SleepThread();
        RunThread t2 = new RunThread();

        t1.start();
        t2.start();
    }
}

✅ Expected Output
SleepThread started
RunThread is running
SleepThread woke up

🧠 What’s Happening?
t1 → goes to sleep state for 2 seconds
t2 → executes immediately
Both run concurrently
🎯 Interview Explanation (Important)

Here, two threads are created. One thread uses Thread.sleep() to pause execution for a fixed time, 
while the other thread executes normally. This demonstrates how multiple threads can run independently and concurrently.
